The paper deals with the problem of blur detection in images using deep learning-based methods. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also involves the use of self-supervised learning, which is a popular topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of object proposals and synthetic blur generation involves graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, and cs.MM.
